    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="505"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received April 29.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 501.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 402, of the 30th ultimo, has
                    been received, and I have the honor to inform you that the result has justified
                    my conclusion not to send Mr. Jewett to Bitlis. I chose rather to rely for
                    security on the promise of the Porte, made on my emphatic demand for a telegram
                    to every governor and military commander in Asia Minor to enforce respect and
                    protection for our citizens. An increased feeling of security in the interior
                    shows that the order was sent.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
